{
  "text": "Already a long time ago [CITATION_1] it was shown that the belt trick implies the Dirac equation. Battey-Pratt and Racey deduced this result by exploring a rotating object connected by strands (tails) to spatial infinity , in the way shown in Figure 4 . In their approach, the rotating object plus the (unobservable) tails would correspond to a microscopic particle. (In the strand model, the central object becomes the tangle core.) An object that is continuously rotating is described by a phase; Battey-Pratt and Racey could show that this phase obeys the Dirac equation in free space, if antiparticles are added.",
  "citation_candidates": [
